    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, the Austin Waves look to capitalize on a favorable environment for our high-upside speed threats. The engine of today\u2019s lineup is **Jackson Merrill** (74.85) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (74.84), who stand as our most potent options. **Jackson Merrill** benefits immensely from his leadoff placement and a high-efficiency matchup against Taillon, while **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** is positioned for a massive performance against Bello, buoyed by an elite BvP track record (33 PA) and strong park factors. **Kyle Tucker** (73.39) remains a must-start, providing the necessary floor in our 5x5 build, while **Josh Lowe** (71.68) is a fascinating play; his score is significantly elevated by Fedde\u2019s slow delivery, which provides a massive advantage for **Josh Lowe** to hunt stolen bases\u2014the scarcest commodity in our league.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Marcell Ozuna** (57.35), who finished as our highest-rated reserve. Despite a solid projection against Pallante, **Marcell Ozuna** was edged out by the superior plate efficiency of players like **Jacob Wilson** (65.23) and **Andy Pages** (64.01), both of whom benefit from superior park factors and more favorable platoon splits today. We are also navigating a significant roster void with **Gunnar Henderson** sidelined due to a rainout and **Jordan Westburg** remaining on the IL, placing additional pressure on our starters to maintain our 5x5 pace. Investors should note that **Drake Baldwin** faces the stiffest test of the day against a dominant Skubal (2.71 xERA); while his 46.72 score suggests he is a marginal play, we are keeping him in the lineup to preserve our game caps while betting on his second-spot position to mitigate the elite SP risk.",
